This paper is about Natural Language Understanding (NLU) in Spoken Dialogue Systems, which falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses neural networks for the NLU task, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of CRF tagging layers, which is a statistical modeling technique commonly used in Sequence Labeling (cs.SD). Finally, the paper discusses the improvement in entity tagging F-score, which is a metric commonly used in Natural Language Processing (cs.NE).
